{"quote": "The angels sing in his legs", "page_title": "Roberto Baggio", "page_bio": "Roberto Baggio (18 February 1967) is a retired football in Italy Forward (association football) and Attacking Midfielder (football)/playmaker who was the former President of the Technical Sector of the FIGC. Widely regarded as one of the greatest footballers of all time, he came fourth in the FIFA Player of the Century#FIFA internet vote Internet poll, and was chosen as a member of the FIFA World Cup Dream Team. In 1993, Baggio was named FIFA World Player of the Year and won the Ballon dOr. In 2004, he was named one of the FIFA 100 as part of FIFA 100th anniversary celebration. He is the only Italian ever to score in three FIFA World Cup, 1990, 1994 and 1998, and holds the record for most goals scored in World Cup tournaments for Italy, along with Paolo Rossi and Christian Vieri.", "page_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roberto Baggio"}